        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 2:13AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 212 AM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 7 miles north of
Granville, or 23 miles northeast of Minot, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Granville, Upham, Deering, and Denbigh.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
